    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" subtype="diplomatic" ana="b1">
                <p>ΙΩΣΗΠΟΥΕΛΕΑ<lb/>ΖΑΡΟΥΤΟΥΣΕΙΛΟΥ<lb/>ΩΡΗΣΟΥ</p>
            </div>
            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Yosef, son of Eleazar, son of Shila, of Ḥorsha</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The inscription indicates that the mausoleum belonged to a wealthy Jewish family
                    that came from the southern Hebron hill country (Horsha/Hurisa). They apparently
                    arrived in Tiberias in the wake of the Bar Kokhba uprising. It is possible that
                    the name Shila is also related to the Bar-Silni family, a wealthy Tiberian
                    family that appears in Talmudic sources. </p>
            </div>
        </body>
